ng to longer-term plans with an outcome focus would provide a better way of achieving the intended goals. This change could be implemented through forthcoming legislation, allowing for improved monitoring and evaluation of fee and access plans' success.&#10;&#10;In summary, integrating fee and access plans into outcome agreements can help shift the focus from inputs to outputs, making it easier to assess their effectiveness. To achieve this, a restructuring of the current format is required, moving towards longer-term, outcome-focused plans that can be effectively monitored and evaluated through legislation.">
