ropriate regulation and accountability of institutions for their public funding and the privileges they enjoy. They aim to ensure national priorities are clearly articulated through remit letters and other levers, while maintaining a positive working relationship with higher education institutions and HEFCW. The post-compulsory education and training Bill may include provisions to address these concerns.">
