ities' governing bodies, while women account for only 44%, and BME (Black and Minority Ethnic) representation is as low as 4%. This lack of diversity may lead to biased decision-making, limited perspectives, and missed opportunities to engage with diverse communities. The Welsh Government has identified this issue as a concern and aims to address it in the PCET Bill by promoting diversity and inclusion in governance arrangements.">
