ork-based and part-time postgraduate learning, the government will ensure that quality assurance regimes evolve accordingly. Historically, work-based learning quality assurance has been Estyn's responsibility, while university assurance regimes have fallen under the QAA's purview. Greater synergy in quality assurance and enhancement across these different areas of activity is encouraged.&#10;&#10;5. The Welsh government will maintain institutional autonomy while ensuring appropriate regulation and accountability for public funding and privileges in higher education, aiming to move things forward effectively and address emerging trends in the sector.">
