    <edge source="The Welsh government has not identified an urgent reason or pressing policy need to regulate part-time and postgraduate fees through fee limits in the new legislation because the current Act, the 2015 Act, does not permit fee regulation for most postgraduate courses. In the case of part-time courses, the government is currently content that fee levels are not exceeding the amount of student support made available by the Welsh Government. The success of attracting people to postgraduate and part-time study in Wales is due to the reforms to student finance, which the government wants to continue supporting. While they will keep this issue under review, there is no current review of this policy mentioned in the transcript." target="yes, according to the transcript, the Welsh Government is planning to review and potentially amend or replace the Higher Education (Wales) Act 2015 through the post-compulsory education and training Bill. However, they did not explicitly mention plans to repeal the Act. The new bill may include provisions to ensure appropriate regulation and accountability of institutions for their public funding and privileges.">
